This script detects introgressed genomic blocks in individual genomes using per-site parental allele information and provides SNP-level outputs suitable for chromosome painting and downstream visualization.

It is designed for population genomic datasets where, two parental populations are represented by fixed alleles (p1, p2), individuals have phased or unphased genotypes (0|0, 0|1, 1|1, .|.), introgression is inferred from the presence of the foreign parental allele relative to each individual’s background ancestry.

In addition to block detection, the script can optionally mask SNP genotypes outside introgressed blocks, allowing clean SNP-level visualization (as to continue the plotting with analysis_of_introgression_with_snp_data/src/plot_fixed_site_gts.rb) while keeping a consistent set of genomic positions across individuals.

Features

Detect introgressed blocks per individual using a sliding-window approach

Flexible definition of introgression: foreign homozygotes only, or foreign allele present in heterozygotes.

Filters blocks by:

minimum SNP count

missing genotype proportion

proportion of non-introgressed SNPs

Outputs per-individual block files

Creates a filtered SNP table containing only positions inside any introgressed block across all individuals

Optional SNP-level masking: for each individual, genotypes outside that individual’s blocks are replaced by the expected background homozygote number and coordinates of SNPs remain unchanged.

Designed for chromosome painting and comparative visualization across individuals

Input Requirements
1. SNP table (TSV) (can be generated from VCF file with: https://github.com/mmatschiner/tutorials/blob/master/analysis_of_introgression_with_snp_data/src/get_fixed_site_gts.rb)

Must contain at least these columns:

Column	Description
Chromosome	Scaffold / chromosome name
Position	Genomic position (bp)
p1	Parental allele (0/1)
p2	Parental allele (0/1)
<individual IDs>	Genotypes (`0

Example:

Chromosome  Position  p1  p2  10007  10008
sc01        3790697   0   1   0|1    0|0

2. Background map

Defines the background ancestry of each individual.

Whitespace-separated file with two columns:

10007  p1
10008  p2


p1 means background allele is taken from column p1

p2 means background allele is taken from column p2

How Introgression Is Defined

For each individual and SNP, the foreign allele is the parental allele not matching the individual’s background.

a SNP is introgressed if:

it is homozygous for the foreign allele, or (optionally) heterozygous and contains the foreign allele.

Blocks are built by:

scanning with a sliding SNP window, extending while introgressed SNPs remain close in genomic distance and stopping after two consecutive non-introgressed SNPs (configurable for missing data). Window size w sets the tolerance for noise by allowing up to (w − 1) non-introgressed or missing SNPs between introgressed SNPs during block seeding; smaller w enforces stricter clustering, larger w allows sparser introgressed signal.

Usage

python block_filters.py \
  -c input_snps.tsv \
  -i 10007,10008,10009 \
  --background_map background_map.tsv \
  -w 3 \
  --max_distance 3000 \
  --min_snps 5 \
  --max_missing_prop 0.2 \
  --max_nonintro_prop 0.5 \
  --count_hetero_as_introgressed \
--filtered_snps_out filtered_snps_masked.tsv \
  --mask_outside_blocks

                                                    
This will overwrite each individual’s genotypes outside their introgressed blocks in the input fixed sites file with the expected background homozygote

Optional:

--mask_missing_too


also masks missing genotypes (.|.) outside blocks.


Outputs
1. Per-individual block files

For each individual:

blocks_<INDIVIDUAL>_w<WINDOW>.tsv


Columns include:

Chromosome

Individual

Start, End

Lenght (bp)

counts of genotype classes

N_SNPs

Non_introgressed

2. Filtered SNP table

Contains only SNPs that fall inside any introgressed block across all individuals.

Same Chromosome/Position set for all individuals


If masking is enabled, genotypes outside blocks are altered, row count and coordinates remain unchanged.


